                    <h5>What is Maryland Healthy Smiles Dental Program?</h5>
                    <p>Maryland Healthy Smiles Dental Program is Maryland's Medicaid Dental Program. This program is for
                        children, pregnant women, and adults in the Rare and Expensive Case Management (REM) Program.
                        The program is here to help you stay healthy.</p>
                    <p>Through the Maryland Healthy Smiles Dental Program, you or your child will receive the same
                        dental benefits as in the past. The Maryland Healthy Smiles Dental Program is managed by
                        DentaQuest of Maryland, LLC. DentaQuest will work with you to make sure you or your child will
                        receive dental health care. DentaQuest will help you find a dentist that participates in the
                        program and is close to your home, and will help you make an appointment, if needed. If you have
                        any questions about the dental program call (888) 696-9596.</p>
                    <h5>Get More Information:</h5>
                    <p>Visit the MD Healthy Smiles home page for more information on the program. Our office actively
                        participates in the program. For additional details you can visit our faq page.</p>
                    <h5>Transportation Information:</h5>
                    <p>Maryland Healthy Smiles Dental Program may cover a ride to dental appointments. Call the
                        Transportation Coordinator at your Local Health Department (LHD) for assistance. If you do not
                        know how to contact your LHD, call the Maryland Healthy Smiles Program Customer Service at:
                        (888) 696-9596 between the hours of 7:30am to 6:00pm or visit the website at
                        www.dentaquestgov.com.</p>
                    <h5>Transportation Schedules:</h5>
                    <p>If you would prefer to download a pdf of available transportation options you can find one on the
                        new patients page of our website.</p>
